{
  "answer": "**The speaker claims that his life consists solely of playing the game of love.**[^1]\n\nThis is the opening couplet of the ghazal, where \"shughl-e-ishq-baazi\" (literally, \"the occupation/business of love-play\") is rendered poetically as the entirety of his existence, questioning the distinction between the real and the illusory.\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/20-hum-hain-aur-shughl-e-ishq-baazi-hai/translation/#p-f826e7).",
